TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR UNPACK & WIN EVENT BY DOWELL
AIM OF THE EVENT :- 
A “ Unpack and Win Event’', is a concept of Dowell.This is to make a video of unpacking the product, demonstration of the first use of the product, and disposal/reusing/ storage of the package. The Video can be related to any specific product.

DETAILS OF THE EVENT :- 
Location:  Online (Mega drive)
Contact: DoWell Team Organizer
Email: ops07@dowellresearch.in
Link for the interactive discussion session with Dowell Team or for any further Query:

PARTICIPATION RULES OF EVENT :- 
ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA:
This event is open to  individuals above the age of 16 years.
Participation in the event constitutes Participant’s full and unconditional agreement to and acceptance of these Terms and Conditions (“Terms”). 
The term “you” refers to  the “Participant”.
Employees of Sponsor and its respective parent companies, affiliates, subsidiaries, advertising, promotion, fulfillment or other coordinating agencies, individuals providing services to Sponsor through an outsourcer or temporary employment agency during the Hackathon period, and their respective immediate family members and persons living in their same household, are not eligible to participate in the competition. 
Your Participation: 
i. You can participate as an individual only. 
ii. Teams are not allowed. Sponsor is not responsible for, and will not assist in resolving, any disputes between the participants. 
iii.To participate, you must make a video of the following three steps as mentioned earlier either as a single video or split of three videos with a maximum duration of 30 mins each. 
iii.You must make your own  arrangements of product and equipment and cover all associated costs and expenses. 
iv.You, as a Participant will be required to do the following: 
The challenge is to build a creative and innovative content video using a product and utilization of its packaging. 
All participants (individual digital identity)will receive an individual code using which you will be able to upload the video(s).
 Incomplete Entries may be disqualified. 

 4. REGISTRATION RULES TO THE EVENT:- 
No payment required for registration and participation
Participants wishing to sign up for the eventn must complete the online Registration Form. All Participants in submitting their registration accept the event regulations and grant consent for the handling of their personal information by Dowell
Participants guarantee that the personal information provided upon registration is true and accurate, with no liability being attributed to DoWell in the event of any falsification and/or inaccuracy. Furthermore, inaccurate and/or falsified information can result in disqualification of the participant from the event.
Applications will be screened as per the criteria.


5. JUDGMENT RULES FOR THE HACKATHON
A panel of 4 to 5 people with relevant expertise will be responsible for judging Entries.
Participant’s contribution will be judged on the basis of the quality, innovation and creativity.
The organizer’s judgement is final.
Refer the calculation template for more clarity on the judgement method.
Discontinuing attendees will be considered only upon the stage they have participated.
Only full attendees will be considered for the final assessment.
Prizes to be awarded based on performance in each step and over all performance in the event. 
In the event of a tie, judges will deliberate to determine the winner. Judging will be conducted in a “ fairplay and unbiased ” format, so judges may inspect Entries at any time during the judging period. 


SCORING OF PARTICIPANTS:

The Entries will be judged according to the following criteria: 
(i) originality/creativity (20%); 
(ii) innovation (25%); 
(iii) analytical skills (10%); 
(iv) strategic thinking (15%) and 
(v) practical implementation (30%). 
Participants will be questioned by the AI team of the organizers based on the videos uploaded by them. Each questionnaire will be unique as per the video uploaded by the participants. Entries must Answer the questions asked to them. Judgment will also be based on this process.

